OL,6,FThe statements outlines the long-
OL,7,Flasting impact his inappropriate
OL,8,Fbehaviour has had on their mental
OL,9,Fhealth and wellbeing.
OL,11,FIn mitigation, the court heard Malcolm
OL,12,Faccepted he was in a managerial
OL,13,Fposition and "should have known
OL,14,Fbetter" - and had been deeply impacted
OL,15,Fby what has happened.
OL,17,FSentencing the defendant, the judge
OL,18,Fsaid residents should have felt safe
OL,19,Fand nurtured, instead they were abused
OL,20,Fby the person in charge of their
OL,21,Fwelfare.
